1
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:39,842
Bonjour, monsieur.

2
00:02:40,052 --> 00:02:42,838
Bonjour, madame...and company.

3
00:02:47,477 --> 00:02:48,970
Good afternoon.

4
00:02:49,227 --> 00:02:52,928
As you see, this lovely city
all around us is Paris.

5
00:02:53,232 --> 00:02:57,181
And this lovely park is, of course,
the Bois de Boulogne.

6
00:02:57,444 --> 00:02:58,725
Pardon me.

7
00:03:05,661 --> 00:03:06,692
Who am l?

8
00:03:06,912 --> 00:03:09,533
Well, allow me to introduce myself.

9
00:03:09,831 --> 00:03:12,121
l am Honoré Lachaille.

10
00:03:12,376 --> 00:03:14,120
Born: Paris.

11
00:03:14,378 --> 00:03:15,457
Date:

12
00:03:16,713 --> 00:03:17,876
Not lately.

13
00:03:18,173 --> 00:03:20,795
This is 1 900.
So let's just say. . .

14
00:03:21,051 --> 00:03:23,126
. . .not in this century.

15
00:03:23,386 --> 00:03:24,964
Circumstances:

16
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:26,343
Comfortable.

17
00:03:26,641 --> 00:03:27,636
Profession:

18
00:03:27,892 --> 00:03:31,391
Lover and collector
of beautiful things.

19
00:03:32,062 --> 00:03:33,640
Not antiques, mind you.

20
00:03:33,939 --> 00:03:35,481
Younger things.

21
00:03:39,862 --> 00:03:42,188
Yes, definitely younger.

22
00:03:42,447 --> 00:03:44,985
Married?
What for?

23
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:47,157
Now, please don't misunderstand.

24
00:03:47,453 --> 00:03:50,737
Like everywhere else,
most people in Paris get married.

25
00:03:50,955 --> 00:03:52,331
But not all.

26
00:03:52,583 --> 00:03:56,960
There are some who will not marry
and some who do not marry.

27
00:03:57,337 --> 00:04:01,086
But here in Paris,
those who will not are usually men. . .

28
00:04:01,383 --> 00:04:04,917
. . .and those who do not
are usually women.

29
00:04:05,804 --> 00:04:09,221
Now, for example,
here we find exhibit A:

30
00:04:09,725 --> 00:04:11,135
The married kind.

31
00:04:11,643 --> 00:04:14,016
These ladies stood their ground
And won

32
00:04:14,271 --> 00:04:16,477
And I salute them, every one

33
00:04:21,612 --> 00:04:23,818
Here are some others to behold

34
00:04:24,072 --> 00:04:26,231
For whom the bells have never tolled

35
00:04:26,492 --> 00:04:29,279
Oh, what a poor, defenseless pair

36
00:04:29,536 --> 00:04:31,824
In those pathetic rags they wear

37
00:04:57,981 --> 00:05:00,852
And there is the future.

38
00:05:06,657 --> 00:05:09,064
Someday, each and every one of them. . .

39
00:05:09,576 --> 00:05:11,568
. . .will either be married. . .

40
00:05:12,036 --> 00:05:14,659
. . .or unmarried.
How adorable they are!

41
00:05:14,957 --> 00:05:16,915
Each time I see a little girl

42
00:05:17,209 --> 00:05:19,285
Of 5 or 6 or 7

43
00:05:19,670 --> 00:05:21,876
I can 't resist the joyous urge

44
00:05:22,256 --> 00:05:24,924
To smile and say thank heaven

45
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,877
For little girls

46
00:05:28,971 --> 00:05:31,971
For little girls
Get bigger every day

47
00:05:34,059 --> 00:05:36,811
Thank heaven for little girls

48
00:05:38,980 --> 00:05:42,184
They grow up
In the most delightful way

49
00:05:43,985 --> 00:05:47,236
Those little eyes
So helpless and appealing

50
00:05:48,282 --> 00:05:52,493
One day will flash and send you
Crashing through the ceiling

51
00:05:53,453 --> 00:05:56,455
Thank heaven for little girls

52
00:05:58,667 --> 00:06:00,375
Thank heaven for them all

53
00:06:00,586 --> 00:06:03,291
No matter where
No matter who

54
00:06:03,589 --> 00:06:06,459
Without them
What would little boys do?

55
00:06:08,344 --> 00:06:09,803
Thank heaven

56
00:06:10,805 --> 00:06:12,346
Thank heaven

57
